{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-242-whats-new-in-core-data"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Data is a framework that you can use to manage the model layer objects in your application, providing generalized and automated solutions to common tasks associated with object life cycle, object graph management, and persistence. Learn about the latest advancements in and explore best practices for taking full advantage of this powerful framework."}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Related Sessions"},{"type":"links","style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-719-Optimizing-IO-for-Performance-and-Battery-Life"]}]}],"metadata":{"title":"What’s New in Core Data","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC16","role":"sampleCode"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/242\/","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-242-Whats-New-in-Core-Data","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"title":"WWDC16","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16","type":"topic"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-203-Whats-New-in-Cocoa","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-203-whats-new-in-cocoa","type":"topic","title":"What’s New in Cocoa","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS brings many new enhancements such as automatic window tabbing, enhanced color reproduction, and improved presentation of right-to-left languages. Get introduced to new APIs for these features and more, such as NSGridView and NSMeasurement. Learn about new conventions for APIs in Swift and Objective-C. This is your first stop to discover exciting new features in Cocoa sessions throughout the week."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift":{"title":"What’s New in Swift","abstract":[{"text":"Hear about the newest features in Swift 3, the third major release of the safe, fast, and expressive language, and the first major release built with the open source community. Gain insight into the latest changes in Xcode including enhanced migration support to help move your code to Swift 3. Learn how you can get involved in the open source community at Swift.org.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-402-whats-new-in-swift","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-719-Optimizing-IO-for-Performance-and-Battery-Life":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gain specific insights into tuning your application for better I\/O performance. Learn best practices to reduce local storage operations and trim your memory usage. Get details on how to update your app to increase responsiveness and extend battery life."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-719-Optimizing-IO-for-Performance-and-Battery-Life","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","title":"Optimizing I\/O for Performance and Battery Life","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-719-optimizing-io-for-performance-and-battery-life"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}]},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2016/242/":{"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/242\/","checksum":null,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/242\/","type":"download"},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg